    public abstract class ObjectParameterVisitorAdapter<T>
extends Object
implements IObjectParameterVisitor<T>
    Adapter Implementors of this class can choose which types they want to handle. Extending this class instead of implementing the IObjectParameterVisitor interface directly has the following advantages:
  • only the required types need to be handled
  • adding of further visit methods to the IObjectParameterVisitor interface in the future, will not lead to source code incompatibilities in subclasses of this adapter
